verbose_text: The principal cells of the striatum are GABAergic spiny projection neurons (SPNs) that can be divided into two subtypes : striatonigral neurons of the direct pathway (dSPNs) that express type 1 dopamine receptors (D1) and striatopallidal neurons of the indirect pathway (iSPNs) that express type 2 dopamine receptors (D2).
